Zambia+
Zimbabwe(1992)
Countries not reporting status even once in the 4 years:
Chad, DR Congo, Mali, Mauritania, Niger, Sao Tome & Principe, Tanzania (but
note "African swine fever - Tanzania (Dar es Salaam) 20010529.1039") and
Gabon said it didn't know its status but the disease was suspected (?).
Never ever had it (0000 in all four years):
Algeria, Burkino Faso, Egypt, Lesotho, Libya, Mauritius, Morocco, Reunion,
Sudan, Swaziland, Tunisia.
There is patently a widespread risk of this wildlife disease infecting
domestic swine in many countries in Africa. - Mod.MHJ
